        "text": "Effect [ edit | edit source ] Main article: Substitute doll Effect Shed Tail creates a substitute at the cost of half of the user's maximum HP (rounded up), then switches the user out . The created substitute has 1/4 of the user's maximum HP. The Pokemon that switches in will then have the substitute. If the user is holding a Berry that would trigger in response to Shed Tail (such as a Sitrus Berry ), it eats its held Berry before switching out. Shed Tail fails (and will not switch the user out) if the user already has a substitute, if the user has no teammates to switch to, or if the user's HP is less than or equal to 50% of its maximum HP. The substitute will not protect the sent out Pokemon against entry hazards .",
